Build a dashboard page in the frontend of this repo, following the existing project patterns.

Goal:
Create a visual page editor for the authenticated tenant.

Available backend endpoints:
- `PATCH /api/pages/:pageName/component/content`
  body: `{ data: fullDataObject }`
  effect: replaces whole `component.data`
- `PATCH /api/pages/:pageName/component/preference`
  body: `{ preference: fullPreferenceObject }`
  effect: replaces whole `component.preference`
- `GET /api/pages/by-tenant`
  effect: returns all pages for the authenticated tenant
- `PATCH /api/pages/:pageName/components/:componentType/disable`
  effect: sets `enabled=false` in `pages.components`
- `DELETE /api/pages/by-name/:pageName`
  effect: deletes page and cascades component row delete
-be free to explore and use already created backendpoints rather than doing gimmics

UI requirements:
- Build the UI server side component in /editor
- Left side: a sidebar/nav listing all tenant pages.
- Left/main editor panel: a dynamic form editor for the selected page.
- Right side: a live visual preview of the page, like a website preview.
- The editor must allow editing any field found in page content props and preference props.
- When the user focuses a field in the editor, the preview should scroll to the related section being edited.
- When the user leaves a field (`onBlur`), save changes immediately using the correct endpoint.
- Content edits must call the content endpoint.
- Preference/style edits must call the preference endpoint.
- Component disable actions must call the disable endpoint.
- Page delete actions must call the delete endpoint.

Architecture expectations:
- page.tsx and components folder keep files not exceeding 100 lines
- Reuse tenant visual components for the preview 
-get inspiration from editor/demo just smthing simple like 
- Prefer a clean structure  human like in the repo now over quick duplication.

Behavior details:
- On load, fetch tenant pages from `GET /api/pages/by-tenant`.
- Selecting a page loads it into the editor and preview.
- The form should be generated dynamically from the selected page data structure rather than hardcoded per page.
- anything existng in preferences and data objects is editable so explore that to know how to create the form that edits
- Save on blur, not on every keystroke.

Acceptance criteria:
- User can switch between tenant pages from the sidebar.
- User can edit content and see the preview update immediately.
- User can edit preferences and see the preview update immediately.
- User can disable a component and the preview reflects it.
- User can delete a page from the dashboard.
- Saving happens automatically on blur.
- The implementation fits the repo’s existing patterns and code style.

Before coding, inspect the current frontend structure and choose the best place for the dashboard editor and preview composition.
